topic.prompt: Talk about a specific family tradition that you love (or find totally weird).

messages.text: I like coming home for Christmas, which is a good breather for the year
I think our family does a pretty good job of balancing the energy of home for christmas with the need to be home
Yep, and at least always one hotpot meal since mom doesn't want to cook all the time. Not that I'm complaining or anything
I do remember one year where my dad made like a whole duck dinner for christmas
Duck is definitely my favorite, but that was too much of a good thing. There is a limit for how much duck I want to consume
I think its very underrated, but a lot of people think its too much of a good thing (I mean, I think you can do a roast duck on thanksgiving dinner or something and it would be fine)
